subproject.description:
The GEF SGP started its first contacts with UNDP Cape Verde in 2006. In mid-2008, a mission was conducted to assess the country’s capabilities to implement the program, which became operational in August 2009. 
The operationalization of the program provides for a number of key activities including the development of a Country Program Strategy (CPS). This document articulates the country’s environmental needs and priorities (including cross-cutting issues such as poverty reduction and gender equality) with commitments made at international level.
subproject.title: APPUI AU  SGP
